procstep.procdesc: Data table dervied from Puget Sound Fresh website was imported to GIS layer. Data was manipulated to conform to COMMON_INTEREST core schema. Items not part of core schema were added to a business table for this topic. Data was imported to respective core and business tables. Featureclass FARMERS_MARKETS_POINT was generated using standard python routine to create children featureclasses from COMMON_INTEREST and associated business tables.

Updated against list provided by Puget Sound Fresh website. Spreadsheet contained 74 records, only 52 of these records were updated to the FARMERS_MARKET_POINT featureclass. Rejected records include those whose geographic location falls outside bounds set for King County area of interest. Records from PSF spreadsheet reformatted to align to schema for COMMON_INTEREST, but all original data values preserved. Original data in COMMON_INTEREST was truncated for this domain and reloaded; therefore FEATURE_ID values are not preserved during reload.

Updated against list provided by Puget Sound Fresh website. Spreadsheet contained 74 records, only 52 of these records were updated to the FARMERS_MARKET_POINT featureclass. Rejected records include those whose geographic location falls outside bounds set for King County area of interest. Records from PSF spreadsheet reformatted to align to schema for COMMON_INTEREST, but all original data values preserved. Original data in COMMON_INTEREST was truncated for this domain and reloaded; therefore FEATURE_ID values are not preserved during reload.

Updated against list provided by Puget Sound Fresh (PSF) website. Spreadsheet contained 86 records, 14 of which had no coordinate location information. No attempt was made to geocode any of these by address as they fell outside the area of interest. Of the remaining (86-14=72) only 50 of these were updated to the FARMERS_MARKET_POINT featureclass. Rejected records include those whose geographic location falls outside bounds set for King County area of interest. Records from PSF spreadsheet was reformatted to align to schema for COMMON_INTEREST and to COMMON_INTEREST_FM businesst table. However, all original data values were preserved. Original data in COMMON_INTEREST was truncated for this domain and reloaded; therefore FEATURE_ID values are not preserved during reload.
